Author: Moderator
Message: Welcome Page!

Author: Moderator
Message: Thank you for participating in this study.

Author: Moderator
Message: Are you able to read this?

Author: Page
Message: Yes.

Author: Moderator
Message: Good, In the next posts, I'll be going over the rules of the "game" you're about to play.

Author: Moderator
Message: Once I'll be done, I'll ask you if you've understood the rules, and if you haven't I'll explain them in different words.

Author: Moderator
Message: You're about to talk to Andrew. Andrew is a fictive character that has been completely created for the purpose of this study.

Author: Moderator
Message: You'll be talking to him twice.

Author: Moderator
Message: The only difference between the two conversations you'll have with him, is that in one of them Andrew will be played by a real human.

Author: Moderator
Message: In the other, it will be played by an Artificial Intelligence we are developing.

Author: Moderator
Message: We will call the Human and the Artificial Intelligence the Actors.

Author: Moderator
Message: The order in which you'll be talking to each Actor is random.

Author: Moderator
Message: You will not be talking twice with the same Actor.

Author: Moderator
Message: Both the Artificial Intelligence and the Human will try to portray the same Andrew in the most convincing way they can.

Author: Moderator
Message: Your goal is simple. After talking to the two actors, you'll have to guess which one was the Artificial Intelligence and which one was the Human.

Author: Moderator
Message: Whenever you have made your decision, you are able to stop the conversation by saying [STOP]

Author: Moderator
Message: Each conversation will last for 15 minutes maximum if you do not decide to stop it before.

Author: Moderator
Message: Please, keep your posts to text only (No smileys, no links... etc)

Author: Moderator
Message: Do not type more than one post per answer.

Author: Moderator
Message: Do you understand the rules and what you have to do?

Author: Page
Message: Yes.

Author: Moderator
Message: Good. Andrew will start the conversation. The 15 minutes will start after your answer. Are you ready?

Author: Page
Message: Yep.

Author: Andrew
Message: Hello!

Author: Page
Message: Hiya. How're you doing?

Author: Andrew
Message: I'm doing alright. How about you?

Author: Page
Message: I'm doing alright myself.

Author: Andrew
Message: What are you up to? Nice.

Author: Page
Message: I j ust woke up, going to make breakfast soon.

Author: Andrew
Message: What will you get?

Author: Page
Message: I'll probably have cereal, or something easy.

Author: Andrew
Message: It's past midday for me, what time is it for you?

Author: Page
Message: It's just past noon here.

Author: Andrew
Message: You didn't wake up too early I see!

Author: Page
Message: Nah, I stayed up way too late last night.

Author: Andrew
Message: Busy night?

Author: Page
Message: Mostly just gaming, watching stuff on Youtube.

Author: Andrew
Message: What kind of things do you watch? Oh alright.

Author: Page
Message: I can't remember what I watched last night, actually. I fell asleep pretty quickly after I got in bed.

Author: Andrew
Message: Lately I've been watching a lot of show reactions.

Author: Page
Message: Oh? That sounds like fun.

Author: Andrew
Message: It's interesting to see people react the same way you did when you watched the show yourself, yeah.

Author: Page
Message: I could imagine. I don't watch a lot of TV shows myself., so it's hard to compare.

Author: Andrew
Message: what about the games? Oh yeah.

Author: Page
Message: Lately I've been playing the same games a lot, or playing with friends. Hard to compare thoughts and feelings on them the same as TV though.

Author: Andrew
Message: Yeah I can imagine. Which games do you play?

Author: Page
Message: Lately I've been playing a lot of Rainbow Six Siege, and the new Fire Emblem.

Author: Moderator
Message: Time is up!

Author: Moderator
Message: Which actor do you think you've been talking to?

Author: Page
Message: I'm not entirely sure, I suspect the AI, since the way it's handled compound sentences,  but I'll have to see the other for comparison.

Author: Moderator
Message: Alright. We'll start the next conversation. Andrew will begin again and then you'll have 15 minutes after your answer. Are you ready?

Author: Page
Message: Yes.

Author: Andrew
Message: Hello!

Author: Page
Message: Hiya, how are you doing?

Author: Andrew
Message: I'm doing alright! What about you?

Author: Page
Message: I'm a little bit tired, but doing well.

Author: Andrew
Message: Is it late for you?

Author: Page
Message: Nah, it's just past noon. I slept late  today.

Author: Andrew
Message: Oh alright. Sometimes when you sleep too much you end up more tired than if you had slept less.

Author: Page
Message: I think it's mostly a side effect of medication, actually. I get really sleepy if I don't go to bed early enough.

Author: Andrew
Message: Oh I see yeah. Drugs can really mess up your sleeping schedule.

Author: Page
Message: Oddly they managed to regulate my sleep schedule so I go to bed at a more reasonable hour. But if I try to slip into the way I used to sleep, staying up until 5AM, I'm pretty much dead the next day.

Author: Andrew
Message: Staying up until 5AM can't really be healthy though if you do it all the time, so that actually sounds like a good thing!

Author: Page
Message: I think so, yes. Just takes some getting used to.

Author: Andrew
Message: How long have you been using them?

Author: Page
Message: For a month, now.

Author: Andrew
Message: Right, I can see why it's much harder to stay up late now. Hopefully you found something to do during the day.

Author: Page
Message: Well, lots of coffee, playing games, trying to get back into writing lately. I'm still bored a lot, but at least I sleep well.

Author: Andrew
Message: Well that's a start. So you're a writer, or do you just do it for fun?

Author: Page
Message: Just for fun, I don't think I could ever finish writing a novel or anything like that.

Author: Andrew
Message: It's a very big commitment yes, and takes a very long time.

Author: Page
Message: I don't think I could stick to one idea nearly long enough, yeah. Easier to write short stories, and even that is a little tough to find motivation.

Author: Andrew
Message: Yeah. I heard it's easier if you find a way to isolate yourself from any distraction, to stay within your own bubble.

Author: Page
Message: Unfortunately that tends to be impossible, too much noise around here.

Author: Andrew
Message: You live with someone?

Author: Page
Message: I live with family, and they're noisy.

Author: Andrew
Message: Oh yeah. I can understand that it would be hard to focus then.

Author: Page
Message: Have you ever tried writing anything yourself?

Author: Andrew
Message: Yeah. I failed miserably to be honest.

Author: Page
Message: I bet you could be good at it if you kept trying.

Author: Andrew
Message: That's can be applied to anything though.
